This sauce has a wonderful mix of salt, garlic, chili, and that "je ne sais quoi" of ground dried shrimp or something.<br /><br />My kids spoon it generously into our stir fry dishes--hot but not too hot.<br /><br />Lots of restaurants around here--Cantonese dim sum places--make their own versions, but none is better than this simple jarred sauce.<br /><br />Here in Oakland, CA, we have an old Hong Kong/Cantonese Chinatown where a couple grocers usually carry it, and our suburban-style full-line Asian supermarket, Ranch 99 Market, also stocks it. As you can tell, we find it worth searching for.
